*********************************************************************
THEZZAZZGLITCH'S BIG TRAINER LIST FOR POKéMON RED/BLUE 
*********************************************************************

This list does not only list all the trainers in the game, but also
all (14336 to be exact) of their possible loadouts.

*********************************************************************
FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS
*********************************************************************

Q: What is a 'roster #00'? Why is it at the end?
A: The game has a small programming error, where loading a roster
   with id 0 causes the game to load an unexistent roster 256
   instead. Since these rosters are different than the others,
   there's no reason not to include them in this file too.
   
Q: Which of the rosters cause the ZZAZZ glitch?
A: Every roster which has no Pokémon (which is empty).

Q: How can I get these rosters to appear?
A: There are 4 ways to do so in Red/Blue:

   1. Gameshark, obviously. Modify the trainer with 01XX59D0, and
   change the roster with 01XX5DD0.
   
   2. Mew/Ditto Glitch: Lowering or increasing the attack modifier
   of a found Ditto will allow you to change the roster of a
   trainer you will encounter:
   > Growl at Ditto 2 times: Roster 5 will be loaded.
   > Make Ditto uses Swords Dance 1 time: Roster 9 will be loaded.
   Of course, you still need a right special stat to make the
   correct trainer appear.
   
   3. Old Man glitch: Encountering a trainer on Cinnabar coast
   while still having a loaded roster ID in memory will cause you
   to fight against a roster of a trainer #256.
   Trainer class do not change anything in this case:
   > Fight a Rocket with roster 0x0A first, then encounter a trainer
   > on Cinnabar coast - you will fight roster 0x0A of trainer #256.
   > Fight a Channeler with roster 0x03 first, encounter a trainer
   > on Cinnabar coast - you will fight roster 0x03 of trainer #256.

   4. 8F: With arbitrary code execution, you can access all 14336
   rosters without problem. However, you need to be experienced
   in Z80 assembly if you think about trying this.
   
Q: I tried getting a roster from this list using the Old Man glitch,
   but the roster I got is completely different!
A: Encountering trainers from the Cinnabar coast does not work
   properly - even though you're fighting Prof.Oak/Koga/Rocket, the
   game still thinks you're fighting a trainer with ID 256.
   Read the question above more thoroughly.
   
Q: HOLY CRAP HOW DID YOU MAKE THIS LIST
A: I wrote a small C++ program to do all that stuff for me.

Q: How do I open/search this file? It's way too huge.
A: First of all, you should get a text editor that allows you
   to work with big files smoothly. Notepad probably won't do.
   WordPad is with every Windows computer and works pretty well.
   If you want to find a specific trainer, just search for this:
   ">>> TRAINER (insert hex here)"
   Then scroll until you see a roster you want.
   The only exception is the entry for trainer #256, called:
   ">>> TRAINER 256"
   
Q: All the ZZAZZ trainers have Charizard 'Ms, but there are no
   Charizard 'Ms in their rosters.
A: ZZAZZ corrupts many game variables - including a link battle
   flag, which causes the real roster to be erased. That's why
   you can't see any real loadouts of the ZZAZZ trainers.
   
Q: I used a gameshark code to encounter a trainer. The rosters
   do not appear correctly though.
A: Turn off the gameshark codes after the battle starts :)
